      "content": "I understand your concern, but stopping warfarin abruptly isn't safe and can indeed increase your risk of a stroke. It's crucial to maintain a consistent medication regimen. Since ibuprofen isn't suitable due to its blood-thinning properties, you can try acetaminophen (Tylenol) for pain relief. It doesn't have the same blood-thinning effects and can be used safely with warfarin. However, it's still important to consult your healthcare provider for personalized advice. In the meantime, you can also try applying a cold compress to your forehead to help alleviate the headache. Remember, I'm here to help you find solutions, but always prioritize safety and professional guidance.",
      "source": "target",
