      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can take 500 to 1000 mg of acetaminophen every 4 to 6 hours as needed for pain relief, but don't exceed 3000 mg in 24 hours. This dosage should be safe with warfarin, but always check your warfarin levels and INR (International Normalized Ratio) regularly. If you notice any unusual bleeding or bruising, contact your healthcare provider immediately. Remember, I'm here to help you, but it's always best to consult your doctor for personalized advice.",
      "source": "target",
